

= Self-evaluation

The work was distributed as equally as possible between all the members of the group. We tried to divide the tasks in a fair way, both during the laboratory sessions and when preparing the report.

During the first sessions, the group was divided into two pairs: Inés and Mercedes, and Javier and Rubén. Each pair worked with its own board and microphone, but we also helped each other when it was necessary. This allowed us to compare the results and solve problems more easily.

In the last session, the work of both pairs was joined to test the complete system. The circuits, the DAQ and the LabVIEW program were connected together in order to check the final behaviour of the system.

Mercedes could not attend Session 3, so Inés worked alone during that session. However, she was supported by the rest of the group when needed, and the results were later shared with everyone.

Overall, we think that the main objectives of the laboratory were achieved. We learned how to use the NI-USB-6009 DAQ, acquire and generate signals in LabVIEW, condition MEMS microphone signals and represent the acquired signal in time and frequency domains.

As possible improvements, the wiring could be made cleaner, the noise of the analog circuit could be reduced and the microphones could be calibrated more accurately.